article.headline: Murray State 55, Tennessee Tech 51
article.story: MURRAY, Ky. (AP) -- Darnell Hopkins scored nine points to lead a balanced attack as Murray State beat Tennessee Tech 55-51 Thursday night. Tech (14-6, 9-3 Ohio Valley Conference) came into the contest with a half-game lead over the Racers (12-5, 9-2), but the loss moved Tennessee Tech a half-game behind co-leaders Murray State and Samford. Trey Pearson had seven points for Murray State while Shawn Witherspoon had seven points and eight boards for the Racers. Keyon Boyd came off the bench to score 13 points for Tennessee Tech. Anthony Fisher added eight points for the Golden Eagles. The Racers shot just 36 percent from the floor and were just 3-of-16 from 3-point range but held off the Golden Eagles by shooting 6-of-8 from the line in the final minute. Murray State led by as much as 10 in the second half before Tennessee Tech pulled within a point twice in the final three minutes. But Pearson made four free throws down the stretch to help the Racers win for the eighth time in their last nine games.
